[1] Bangladesh (Rangamati)
Date: Wed 1 Apr 2020
Source: The Daily Star [abridged, edited]
https://www.thedailystar.net/measles-outbreak-in-chattogram-one-more-child-dies-in-rangamati-1888543


One more child died of measles in remote Udolchhari Chakma Para under Sajek union of Rangamati's Baghaichhari upazila early today [1 Apr 2020] taking the death toll in the recent measles outbreak in Chattogram Hill Tracts to 10.

[A 15-year-old child] died at his house around 2:30am, said Nelson Chakma, chairman of Sajek union.

Earlier, 9 children of Tripura and Mro communities died of measles in the remote areas of Rangamati, Bandarban and Khagrachari since 26 Feb 2020.

A 5-member medical team, including an MBBS doctor, went to the affected area this morning [1 Apr 2020], said Md Ahosan Habib, upazila nirbahi officer (UNO) of Baghaichhari Upazila.

"We are going to take some inclusive work plans, including setting up 5 community clinics, sanitation, nutrition, and a water management programme in the affected areas," said the UNO.

"It is true that the EPI programme was not implemented in the measles-affected areas properly as there are some problems," he added.

There are only 2 community clinics for a population of over 16 000 who are mostly from ethnic minority communities in Sajek union, said Ahosan.

The affected children are suffering from serious malnutrition, said Dr Istekhar Ahmed, health officer of Baghaichhari upazila.

The newly measles affected areas in Sajek union are Boroitoli Para, Chip Para, Sath Nong Para, Ujanchaari Para, Shilchhari Para, Kojoichhari Para, Buyachhari Para, Lambabak Para and Bethbunia area, said Nelson Chakma, chairman of the union.

